Language: en

00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:02.980
[Captions by Judy V. at Y Translator]
What types of treats can you
put into a cotton-candy machine

00:00:02.980 --> 00:00:05.460
to make your own custom
flavors of cotton candy?

00:00:05.460 --> 00:00:07.260
In today's video,
we're going to try and find out.

00:00:07.260 --> 00:00:16.040
[Music]

00:00:16.040 --> 00:00:19.100
We've got ourselves a little
home-sized cotton-candy machine,

00:00:19.100 --> 00:00:20.820
and we want to test this out.

00:00:20.820 --> 00:00:22.840
The packaging tells us
that we can actually use

00:00:22.840 --> 00:00:26.440
different kinds of candy to put
directly into our cotton-candy machine

00:00:26.440 --> 00:00:28.330
to have different flavors
when we're finished,

00:00:28.330 --> 00:00:29.280
and we want to test that out.

00:00:29.280 --> 00:00:30.760
We want to see which ones work,

00:00:30.760 --> 00:00:31.840
which ones don't work,

00:00:31.840 --> 00:00:34.120
and if we can use homemade candy,

00:00:34.120 --> 00:00:36.720
that way, we can choose
whatever flavor we want.

00:00:36.720 --> 00:00:37.860
Here's the basic idea.

00:00:37.860 --> 00:00:41.040
We'll first make a batch of cotton
candy using a pre-made sugar

00:00:41.040 --> 00:00:42.660
that's designed for this use.

00:00:42.660 --> 00:00:45.200
We'll then compare that to
regular white sugar

00:00:45.200 --> 00:00:47.060
and a variety of different candies.

00:00:47.340 --> 00:00:49.340
We'll also try our homemade candy recipe,

00:00:49.340 --> 00:00:50.900
and maybe even see if we can get

00:00:50.900 --> 00:00:53.520
some cotton candy that glows
under a black light.

00:00:53.780 --> 00:00:55.920
To start out, let's use the
pre-made cotton-candy sugar

00:00:55.920 --> 00:00:57.240
that you can buy at party stores,

00:00:57.240 --> 00:01:00.120
and see what a normal batch
of cotton candy should look like

00:01:00.120 --> 00:01:02.300
so we can compare
that to other batches later.

00:01:02.300 --> 00:01:04.600
I'm turning it on and letting it spin,
 because it doesn't heat up

00:01:04.600 --> 00:01:06.960
until you hit the switch,
and the one switch does everything.

00:01:06.960 --> 00:01:09.000
So, we're going to let this get warm,
and then we're going to add

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:12.520
about a tablespoon of our
candy floss pre-made sugar

00:01:12.520 --> 00:01:14.280
into the dish and see what we get.

00:01:14.520 --> 00:01:17.840
How cotton candy machines work is
the sugar goes into the little hopper,

00:01:17.840 --> 00:01:20.160
there's a heat source, usually, below it,

00:01:20.160 --> 00:01:22.100
and the heat actually just melt the sugar.

00:01:22.100 --> 00:01:25.380
Once the sugar is melted, it's thrown
out of the sides of the machine.

00:01:25.380 --> 00:01:28.600
Usually, through very
small holes or a very thin gap,

00:01:28.600 --> 00:01:32.020
and the liquid sugar is so thin
that it cools down,

00:01:32.020 --> 00:01:34.260
like, immediately
as it leaves the hopper,

00:01:34.260 --> 00:01:37.700
and so, it just forms into
these super, super fine threads.

00:01:38.090 --> 00:01:40.100
And those just get
thrown out to the side,

00:01:40.100 --> 00:01:42.620
and they stick to the walls,
and you use the cone to gather them up,

00:01:42.620 --> 00:01:43.920
and you eat.

00:01:44.300 --> 00:01:46.720
There, we've got 
some wisps showing up.

00:01:46.720 --> 00:01:52.540
[Music]

00:01:52.540 --> 00:01:55.860
It very much just looks like there's
a lot of busy spiders in there

00:01:55.860 --> 00:01:57.760
that are just building webs really quick.

00:01:57.760 --> 00:02:00.900
You can't really see the threads
as they get thrown out.

00:02:00.900 --> 00:02:03.520
They just sort of look like they're
appearing all of a sudden.

00:02:04.120 --> 00:02:07.880
I think the machine has just about run
its course with the sugar we put in there.

00:02:07.880 --> 00:02:11.740
So, here we have sort of the standard
by which we'll compare other things.

00:02:11.740 --> 00:02:12.800
This is interesting.

00:02:12.800 --> 00:02:17.420
We've just got candy fibers floating
through the air all over the place.

00:02:17.420 --> 00:02:19.480
That's what happens if you use
the pre-made floss sugar

00:02:19.480 --> 00:02:21.960
that's just designed for making cotton candy.

00:02:21.960 --> 00:02:24.100
It looks pretty much just like what
you might think of

00:02:24.100 --> 00:02:27.740
